{"id":398136,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All_the_President%27s_Men_(movie)","text":"\"All the President's Men\" is an Academy Award-winning political thriller movie directed by Alan J. Pakula. It was screen-written by William Goldman. released in 1976. It was based on the 1974 non-fiction book of the same name by Bob Woodward and Carl Bernstein, the two journalists investigating the Watergate scandal for The Washington Post.\nIt stars Robert Redford, Dustin Hoffman, Jason Robards, Martin Balsam, Jack Warden, Ned Beatty, F. Murray Abraham, and Hal Holbrook as \"Deep Throat\". It won four Academy Awards and was nominated for Best Picture. It is part of the United States National Film Registry.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Academy_Award","surface_form":"Academy Award","offset":32},{"uri":"Thriller_movie","surface_form":"thriller movie","offset":64},{"uri":"Alan_J._Pakula","surface_form":"Alan J. Pakula","offset":91},{"uri":"William_Goldman","surface_form":"William Goldman","offset":132},{"uri":"Bob_Woodward","surface_form":"Bob Woodward","offset":229},{"uri":"Carl_Bernstein","surface_form":"Carl Bernstein","offset":246},{"uri":"Watergate_scandal","surface_form":"Watergate scandal","offset":300},{"uri":"The_Washington_Post","surface_form":"The Washington Post","offset":322},{"uri":"Robert_Redford","surface_form":"Robert Redford","offset":352},{"uri":"Dustin_Hoffman","surface_form":"Dustin Hoffman","offset":368},{"uri":"Jason_Robards","surface_form":"Jason Robards","offset":384},{"uri":"Martin_Balsam","surface_form":"Martin Balsam","offset":399},{"uri":"Jack_Warden","surface_form":"Jack Warden","offset":414},{"uri":"Ned_Beatty","surface_form":"Ned Beatty","offset":427},{"uri":"F._Murray_Abraham","surface_form":"F. Murray Abraham","offset":439},{"uri":"Hal_Holbrook","surface_form":"Hal Holbrook","offset":462},{"uri":"Deep_Throat_(Watergate)","surface_form":"Deep Throat","offset":479},{"uri":"Academy_Awards","surface_form":"Academy Awa